# Tool-qual positive case: integer arithmetic + operator precedence.
# Expected value is spec/hand-computed (see .expected sibling), independent of
# the tool under test: 5+6*7=47, 20/6=3 (trunc), 20%7=6, 8-2*3=2.
fn main():
    print(5 + 6 * 7)     # 47  (* binds tighter than +)
    print(20 / 6)        # 3   (integer truncating division)
    print(20 % 7)        # 6   (modulo)
    print(8 - 2 * 3)     # 2
